OL,3,CSon of D-Day's 'Mad Piper' pays
OL,4,Ctribute to heroic father
OL,6,F Emma Wilkinson meets John Millin to
OL,7,Ftalk about his father Bill's
OL,8,Fcourageous actions during the D-Day
OL,9,Flandings.JThe son of a bagpiper who
OL,10,Fplayed as Allied forces scrambled
OL,11,Fashore on D-Day is paying tribute to
OL,12,Fhis father by playing the bagpipes in
OL,13,Fhis garden in the lead-up to the 80th
OL,14,Fanniversary of the Normandy landings.
OL,15,FJohn Millin is playing everyday for
OL,16,Ften days from his home in Rampton,
OL,17,Fnorth Nottinghamshire, in honour of
OL,18,Fhis father, Bill.JBill Millin was a
OL,19,Fcommando who became known as Piper
OL,20,FBill and The Mad Piper due to the way
OL,21,Fhe continued playing under heavy fire
OL,22,Ffrom German forces during the landings
OL,23,Fon 6 June 1944.JHe was the personal
OL,24,Fpiper to Lord Lovat, who became an
OL,25,Fintegral figure on D-Day, and was told
OL,26,Fby the commanding officer to march up
