OL,3,CSon of D-Day's 'Mad Piper' pays
OL,4,Ctribute to heroic father
OL,6,FJohn said his father's memories of the
OL,7,Fday affected him forever.J"He saw some
OL,8,Fof the men he just sailed with over
OL,9,Fthe Channel killed in front of him,"
OL,10,Fhe said.JBill's role in the largest
OL,11,Fseaborne invasion in history was
OL,12,Fcelebrated in the decades that
OL,13,Ffollowed, including in the Academy
OL,14,FAward-winning 1962 film The Longest
OL,15,FDay which depicted the landings.JJohn
OL,16,Fsaid: "The constant reminders affected
OL,17,Fhim psychologically but at the same
OL,18,Ftime he thought, well, if people are
OL,19,Fgoing to focus on the bagpipes then
OL,20,Fthey are not going to forget.J"So
OL,21,Fevery time he played was an act of
OL,22,Fremembrance."
