OL,3,CSon of D-Day's 'Mad Piper' pays
OL,4,Ctribute to heroic father
OL,6,FHaving never picked up the bagpipes to
OL,7,Fplay himself, just two weeks before
OL,8,Fhis father died, John promised Bill he
OL,9,Fwould learn and play one song when a
OL,10,Fstatue was unveiled of Piper Bill in
OL,11,FFrance in 2013.JJohn said: "I think he
OL,12,Fwould have been proud that finally I
OL,13,Fhad picked up the pipes to play."
OL,14,FInvoking a speech Lord Lovat gave to
OL,15,Fhis troops during the Second World
OL,16,FWar, John said: "In a hundred years'
OL,17,Ftime your children's children will
OL,18,Flook back and say, 'they must have
OL,19,Fbeen giants.'"JHe added: "My father
OL,20,Fwas my giant."
